cs.IT, cs.NI, cs.CR, cs.SY, cs.MM

Reasoning: 
1. cs.IT (Information Theory): The paper focuses on secrecy transmission and characterizing the secrecy communication performance, which are key topics in information theory. 
2. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture): The paper considers a wireless network of UAVs and ground receivers/eavesdroppers, which falls under the scope of networking and internet architecture. 
3. cs.CR (Cryptography and Security): The paper deals with secrecy transmission and protection against eavesdropping, which are core topics in cryptography and security. 
4. cs.SY (Systems and Control): The paper optimizes the system configurations (wiretap code rates and UAV positioning altitude) to maximize the secrecy transmission capacity, which involves system design and control. 
5. cs.MM (Multimedia): The paper uses an elevation-angle-dependent line-of-sight (LoS)/non-LoS (NLoS) path-loss model for air-to-ground (A2G) wireless channels, which is related to multimedia signal processing and transmission.
